{"type":"message","id":"94cae6b8","parentId":"4d32d948","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:41.578Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5fo4ojxwjduj_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 130813\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: Python (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. The CFI Compression Experiment was just completed (2026-03-24)\r\n3. Key finding: Three-dimensional filter needed: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n4. Next pending action: \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n5. Another pending: \"Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\"\r\n\r\nLooking at the most recent pulse (pulse_2026-03-24 130714.md), no mutations were applied.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step seems to be:\r\n1. Design/implement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring function\r\n2. Or run the next experiment\r\n\r\nGiven the notes about iteration economics (30-35s per pulse), I should focus on something concrete that advances the compression work.\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is:\r\n- **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI should either:\r\n1. Implement the scoring function in code\r\n2. Design the experiment protocol for Strategy C\r\n3. Update the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with next steps\r\n\r\nLet me pick a concrete action - I'll create a concrete scoring function definition and design the next experiment protocol. This would be documented in the research folder.\r\n\r\nLet me write a focused mutation to advance this work.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis established that a three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) outperforms binary thresholds, but the hybrid scoring formula needs formalization and the next experiment (Strategy C) needs concrete design.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and document the hybrid scoring function and experiment protocol in the synthesis document, providing a clear path to the next iteration.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n``` old_text: **Next experiment:** Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n``` new_text: **Next experiment:** Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring\r\n\r\n### Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, sqrt(freq(T)/120))\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis formula:\r\n- Awards high scores to tokens that are BOTH frequent AND causally predicted\r\n- Penalizes constant-format tokens (high freq, perfect CFI) via sqrt compression\r\n- Rewards research trajectory tokens (moderate freq, high CFI) by combining signals\r\n\r\n### Experiment Design\r\n- **Dataset:** Same 200 pulses from Strategy A/B comparison\r\n- **Metric:** Precision@K and Recall@K for true research tokens\r\n- **Comparison points:**\r\n  - Strategy C score vs binary CFI ≥ 0.5\r\n  - Strategy C score vs three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n- **Hypothesis:** sqrt(freq/120) will correctly down-weight constant-format tokens while preserving research trajectory tokens\r\n``` file: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:08:30\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372181575}}
