{"type":"message","id":"b9cf7a53","parentId":"1dbfd068","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:46.448Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse completed successfully. Let me read the most recent log to get the full details.","thinkingSignature":"bac5c9e8093da10b0395cda53d3948bc1b968bb956c6a8971ab9b86d6494de5f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9uiskw6tzk1c_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 130917.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1523,"output":71,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13731,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774372184640}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f01d8f4","parentId":"b9cf7a53","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:09:46.453Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9uiskw6tzk1c_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 130917\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and recent pulse to understand what needs to be done next.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- CFI Compression Experiment completed with key findings\r\n- Pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n- Need to distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nKey insight from the session:\r\n- Three-dimensional compression filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Compression objective: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Design and implement the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment\r\n2. Or update the synthesis document with the three-dimensional filter spec\r\n\r\nGiven the insights about needing to distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5), I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create a concrete experiment design for the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Or implement the three-dimensional filter\r\n\r\nLet me look at what would be the most concrete single action. The notes mention:\r\n- \"Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\"\r\n\r\nSo the next concrete action would be to design/specify the hybrid scoring experiment or implement it.\r\n\r\nLooking at the research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md - this is where the CFI experiment results are documented. I should either:\r\n1. Create a new experiment script for the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Update the synthesis with the next experiment design\r\n\r\nGiven the instruction to be specific and prefer file edits, let me create an experiment spec/design document for the hybrid scoring approach.\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully - the most concrete action would be to design the hybrid scoring experiment since we have all the insights. Let me create a spec for the next experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI experiment revealed the three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) but didn't validate the hybrid scoring function. Strategy C needs a concrete experiment design before it can be run.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate experiment specification for Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring (Strategy C) based on insights from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md - defining the scoring formula, threshold search space, and evaluation methodology.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24  \r\n**Status:** DESIGN SPEC - pending execution\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nThe binary threshold approach (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) fails because:\r\n- Tokens at boundary values get hard cutoffs\r\n- Linear freq weighting may not match information content\r\n\r\n**Scoring function:** `score(T) = CFI(T)^α × min(1, freq(T)/120)^β`\r\n\r\nWhere α,β ∈ {0.25, 0.5, 1.0, 2.0} - grid search over 16 combinations.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Dataset\r\nSame 200 pulses from CFI experiment (80/20 split).\r\n\r\n### Independent Variables\r\n| Parameter | Values |\r\n|-----------|--------|\r\n| α (CFI exponent) | 0.25, 0.5, 1.0, 2.0 |\r\n| β (freq exponent) | 0.25, 0.5, 1.0, 2.0 |\r\n| threshold | 0.05, 0.10, 0.15, 0.20, 0.25 |\r\n\r\n### Dependent Variables\r\n- Precision: fraction of scored tokens that are \"research trajectory\"\r\n- Recall: fraction of research tokens captured\r\n- F1: harmonic mean\r\n- Compression ratio: tokens_remaining / total_tokens\r\n\r\n### Ground Truth Definition\r\n**Research trajectory token** = appears in 3+ pulses AND does NOT appear in EVERY pulse  \r\n(i.e., freq ∈ [3, 160) with 160 being \"every pulse\" for metaprogramming)\r\n\r\n**Constant format token** = appears in 95%+ of pulses (freq ≥ 152 on 160-pulse corpus)\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcomes\r\n\r\n| Scenario | Predicted Pattern |\r\n|----------|-------------------|\r\n| α=1, β=1 | Matches binary threshold approach |\r\n| α=2, β=1 | CFI heavy - better precision, lower recall |\r\n| α=1, β=2 | Freq heavy - better recall, lower precision |\r\n| α=0.5, β=0.5 | Balanced - moderate both |\r\n\r\n### Key Test Cases\r\n1. **\"Phase 1\"** (freq≈136, CFI≈0.96) → Should score high regardless\r\n2. **\"pulse\"** (freq≈160, CFI≈1.0) → Should be penalized by freq normalization\r\n3. **\"architectur\"** (freq≈40, CFI≈0.85) → Depends on exponents\r\n\r\n## Implementation Sketch\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef hybrid_score(token, cfi, freq, alpha, beta, max_freq=160):\r\n    freq_component = min(1.0, freq / max_freq) ** beta\r\n    return (cfi ** alpha) * freq_component\r\n\r\n# Grid search\r\nbest_f1 = 0\r\nfor alpha in [0.25, 0.5, 1.0, 2.0]:\r\n    for beta in [0.25, 0.5, 1.0, 2.0]:\r\n        for thresh in [0.05, 0.10, 0.15, 0.20, 0.25]:\r\n            # Evaluate F\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:09:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372186452}}
